radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is fluid-filled, dilated measuring 1.1 cm with hyperenhancing walls and surrounding fat stranding. Multiple hypodensities in the right lobe of the liver, uncharacterized but likely cysts. Mild periportal edema noted. Stomach, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and reproductive organs are normal. No evidence of significant vascular or bone abnormalities.
